[{'text': 'The city of Boston stands at the mouths of
the Charles and Mystic Rivers', 'start': 10.87, 'duration': 4.12}, {'text': 'at the East Coast of the United States of America.', 'start': 14.99, 'duration': 3.28}, {'text': 'Situated on the banks of Massachusetts Bay,
Boston features a fine natural harbor.', 'start': 18.27, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': "Boston is a city that's been shaped by the
sea,", 'start': 25.689, 'duration': 2.701}, {'text': "but it's her people who have helped shape
the history of the USA.", 'start': 28.39, 'duration': 4.93}, {'text': 'Since its inception in 1630, Boston has remained
at the epicenter', 'start': 33.32, 'duration': 4.34}, {'text': 'of American political, social, and cultural
life.', 'start': 37.66, 'duration': 4.21}, {'text': "Every street corner, it seems, is a reminder
of Boston's role", 'start': 41.87, 'duration': 3.149}, {'text': 'in The American Revolution.', 'start': 45.019, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'Boston is a compact and highly livable city.', 'start': 54.539, 'duration': 3.66}, {'text': 'There are numerous options to explore Boston,', 'start': 58.199, 'duration': 2.82}, {'text': 'but the best way to discover the city is by
foot -', 'start': 61.019, 'duration': 3.011}, {'text': 'it's nicknamed "the walking city" for good
reason!', 'start': 64.03, 'duration': 4.03}, {'text': "The Freedom Trail is a self-guided walking
tour that's easy to pick up", 'start': 68.06, 'duration': 3.75}, {'text': 'wherever you see the distinctive red markings
on the sidewalk.', 'start': 71.81, 'duration': 3.63}, {'text': 'The two-and-a-half-mile-long trail weaves
its way past sixteen historic sites', 'start': 75.44, 'duration': 5.75}, {'text': "that were instrumental in America's march
to Independence.", 'start': 81.19, 'duration': 4.09}, {'text': 'The trail officially starts in Boston Common,', 'start': 85.28, 'duration': 4.44}, {'text': 'the oldest city park in America and the centerpiece', 'start': 89.72, 'duration': 2.82}, {'text': 'to a string of parks and gardens affectionately
known as "Boston's Emerald Necklace".', 'start': 92.54, 'duration': 6.32}, {'text': 'Highlights of the trail include The State
House,', 'start': 98.86, 'duration': 2.53}, {'text': 'with its gleaming gold dome, and the Granary
Burying Ground,', 'start': 101.39, 'duration': 3.75}, {'text': 'the final resting place of Samuel Adams, Paul
Revere,', 'start': 105.14, 'duration': 3.75}, {'text': "and many of Boston's bravest sons and daughters.", 'start': 108.89, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'Faneuil Hall, often referred to as "The Cradle
of Liberty",', 'start': 116.18, 'duration': 3.53}, {'text': 'was the stage from which Samuel Adams and
James Otis fanned the winds of Revolution.', 'start': 119.71, 'duration': 4.86}, {'text': 'And just behind are the Quincy and Faneuil
Hall Markets,', 'start': 124.57, 'duration': 3.48}, {'text': "two of Boston's most popular places to eat
and hang out.", 'start': 128.05, 'duration': 4.98}, {'text': 'Stop by the 17th century home of Paul Revere,', 'start': 133.03, 'duration': 2.38}, {'text': 'the patriot immortalized for his famous all-night
ride to Lexington,', 'start': 135.41, 'duration': 4.73}, {'text': 'warning that "the British were coming!"', 'start': 140.14, 'duration': 3.489}, {'text': 'Walking across the Charles River brings Freedom
Trail walkers to the Bunker Hill Monument,', 'start': 143.629, 'duration': 4.321}, {'text': 'where the newly-formed colonial army first
stood up to the Red Coats', 'start': 147.95, 'duration': 3.47}, {'text': 'in the American War of Independence.', 'start': 151.42, 'duration': 4.209}, {'text': 'The Trail concludes at one of the most beloved
ships in the United States,', 'start': 155.629, 'duration': 4.61}, {'text': 'the USS Constitution.', 'start': 160.239, 'duration': 2.691}, {'text': 'Launched in 1797, "Old Ironsides" is the world's
oldest commissioned naval vessel afloat.', 'start': 162.93, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'Everywhere along the waterfronts of Boston', 'start': 172.87, 'duration': 2.009}, {'text': "we are reminded of the city's maritime connections;", 'start': 174.879, 'duration': 3.381}, {'text': 'this is a city with salt in its blood.', 'start': 178.26, 'duration': 2.979}, {'text': 'The harbor is also the place to jump aboard', 'start': 181.239, 'duration': 2.4}, {'text': 'the many scenic and whale watch cruises on
offer,', 'start': 183.639, 'duration': 2.671}, {'text': "or to sample the fruits of the sea - Boston's
seafood is so fresh,", 'start': 186.31, 'duration': 4.069}, {'text': "you'd swear it almost leapt onto your plate!", 'start': 190.379, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': "Once you've explored the Freedom Trail, it's
time to simply follow your nose -", 'start': 197.849, 'duration': 4.43}, {'text': 'this is a great city to get lost in!', 'start': 202.279, 'duration': 6.731}, {'text': 'Beacon Hill, with its gas-lit streets and
Federal-style rowhouses,', 'start': 209.01, 'duration': 4.369}, {'text': "is one of Boston's most beautiful neighborhoods.", 'start': 213.379, 'duration': 2.241}, {'text': "In Charles Street, it's easy to lose a few
hours in the antique shops", 'start': 215.62, 'duration': 3.949}, {'text': 'hunting down the perfect souvenir of "Old
Boston".', 'start': 219.569, 'duration': 4.241}, {'text': 'Newbury Street, in neighboring Back Bay,', 'start': 223.81, 'duration': 2.31}, {'text': "is one of America's great shopping avenues,", 'start': 226.12, 'duration': 2.379}, {'text': 'featuring everything from exclusive emporiums
to sidewalk stalls.', 'start': 228.499, 'duration': 5.64}, {'text': 'Back Bay also offers plenty of places to chill
out and reflect, like Copley Square.', 'start': 234.139, 'duration': 5.19}, {'text': 'Or, you could even join a service in Trinity
Church -', 'start': 239.329, 'duration': 3.651}, {'text': 'listed as one of the ten most significant
buildings in the United States.', 'start': 242.98, 'duration': 4.799}, {'text': 'To get even closer to the heavens, and for
the best views of Boston,', 'start': 247.779, 'duration': 5.32}, {'text': 'take the elevator to the Skywalk Observatory
in the nearby Prudential Tower.', 'start': 253.099, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'Boston is a city that owes much to its immigrants', 'start': 260.59, 'duration': 2.579}, {'text': 'who came here filled with hopes, dreams and
traditions.', 'start': 263.169, 'duration': 4.12}, {'text': "These cultures have become part of Boston's
fabric,", 'start': 267.289, 'duration': 2.5}, {'text': 'from the culinary delights of Little Italy,', 'start': 269.789, 'duration': 2.991}, {'text': 'to the Irish pubs which quench the thirst
of this hard-working city.', 'start': 272.78, 'duration': 6.699}, {'text': 'Bostonians like to play hard, and in this
sports-crazy town', 'start': 279.479, 'duration': 3.861}, {'text': "there's no greater hallowed turf than Fenway
Park,", 'start': 283.34, 'duration': 3.99}, {'text': 'home to the Boston Red Sox for 100 years.', 'start': 287.33, 'duration': 6.66}, {'text': 'Culture rates highly in Boston too.', 'start': 293.99, 'duration': 1.53}, {'text': 'The Museum of Fine Arts, with its fabulous
Impressionist Collection', 'start': 295.52, 'duration': 4.399}, {'text': 'houses the largest displays of Monets outside
of France.', 'start': 299.919, 'duration': 5.271}, {'text': "Boston, however, isn't a city that rests on
past glories.", 'start': 305.19, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'There are over 50 colleges and universities
within the greater Boston Area.', 'start': 312.789, 'duration': 5.06}, {'text': 'With prestigious institutions like Harvard
and MIT', 'start': 317.849, 'duration': 5.211}, {'text': 'continuing to produce Presidents and Nobel
Laureates,', 'start': 323.06, 'duration': 3.71}, {'text': 'Boston has blossomed into a city that not
only shapes America, but the entire world.', 'start': 326.77, 'duration': 5.199}]
